and film critic Lindsay Mackie, founded <a href=\"http://filmclub.org\" target=\"&rdquo;_blank&rdquo;\">FILMCLUB</a>,  an educational charity aimed at transforming the lives of young people through film. Through FILMCLUB, schools can screen films at no cost, and afterwards students discuss and review the films. Each week the charity reaches 220,000 children, in over 7,000 clubs.</p><p><a href=\"http://blog.ted.com/2012/06/13/great-films-from-beeban-kidron/\" target=\"_blank\">Read more on the TEDBlog &gt;&gt;</a></p><p>&nbsp;</p>"}],"speaker_name":"Beeban Kidron","tags":["art","children","culture","film","storytelling","youth","movies"],"title":"The shared wonder of film","video_type":{"id":"1","name":"TED Stage Talk"},"viewed_count":799006}]}
